      "body": "The Rust marketplace commands take `AuthenticatedRequest<T>` with `#[serde(flatten)]`, so the payload fields (like `id` and `consented_permissions`) must be at the same level as `auth_token`. `createAuthenticatedRequest` wraps those fields under `payload`, which means the Rust deserializer never sees `id` for install/uninstall/getDetails and will reject the request as missing required fields. This makes the new marketplace actions fail at runtime even with a valid auth token. Consider flattening the payload fields in the request object before invoking Tauri or updating `createAuthenticatedRequest`/Rust to accept a nested `payload`.",
